# Ignore autoreconf TEMPORARY artifacts in the vendored upstream tree.
# These are generated every time build.sh runs autoreconf and must NOT be
# committed (would corrupt vendor integrity: byte-for-byte from tarball).
#
# DO NOT ignore the build-aux/ scripts (install-sh, compile, depcomp,
# missing, etc.) — those are part of the autotools distribution and are
# REQUIRED by configure. They live in build-aux/ in the tarball.
#
# What to ignore:
#   - autom4te.cache/  (autoconf cache, regenerated every build)
#   - configure~       (backup of configure before regeneration)
#   - config_h.in~     (backup of config_h.in)
autom4te.cache/
configure~
config_h.in~
*.o
*.lo
*.a
.deps/
.libs/